{
  "bio": [
    "Cristiano Crippa is the son of Giuseppe Crippa (d. 2025), the late founder of Technoprobe, an Italian manufacturer of probe cards, small devices that test the functionality of microchips.",
    "He cofounded Technoprobe in 1989 alongside his father in his garage and attic, while his father was still working at semiconductor firm ST.",
    "Technoprobe went public on Euronext Milan in 2022; Cristiano owns an 18% stake.",
    "He has served as Technoprobe's chairman of the board since 2017."
